                        <p>The primary healthcare system will be composed of the following subsystems:</p>
                        <div>
                            <p class="list-item"><strong>Registration:</strong> Registration is the initial step where individuals enroll in the primary health care system. It involves creating a record for each individual, including their basic personal and demographic information. This process helps healthcare providers maintain a comprehensive database of patients, which is crucial for managing appointments, tracking medical history, and ensuring continuity of care.</p>
                            <p class="list-item"><strong>Family Planning:</strong> Family planning services involve helping individuals and couples make informed decisions about when to have children, how many children to have, and what methods of contraception to use. These services include providing information about various contraceptive methods, conducting health screenings, and offering counseling about reproductive health. Family planning plays a significant role in promoting reproductive health, preventing unintended pregnancies, and supporting family goals.</p>
                            <p class="list-item"><strong>Prenatal Care:</strong> Pre-natal care is a subset of healthcare services provided to pregnant women before childbirth. It focuses on monitoring the health of both the mother and the developing fetus. Pre-natal care typically includes regular check-ups, medical tests, and screenings to ensure the well-being of the mother and the early detection of any potential complications. It also involves providing guidance on nutrition, exercise, and lifestyle changes during pregnancy.</p>
                            <p class="list-item"><strong>Counselling:</strong> Counseling services within a primary health care system encompass mental health and general wellness support. Trained counselors or mental health professionals offer guidance, support, and interventions to individuals facing psychological or emotional challenges. This can include stress, anxiety, depression, grief, and more. Promoting mental health awareness and providing access to counseling services helps individuals maintain overall well-being.</p>
                            <p class="list-item"><strong>Chronic Medication:</strong> In the realm of chronic medication, healthcare systems focus on providing consistent care and support for individuals dealing with long-term health conditions. Healthcare providers work closely with patients to monitor their conditions, adjust medication regimens as needed, and offer lifestyle recommendations to enhance overall well-being. The goal is to effectively manage chronic illnesses such as diabetes, hypertension, and asthma, enabling patients to lead fulfilling lives while minimizing the impact of these conditions on their daily activities.</p>
                            <p class="list-item"><strong>Vaccinations:</strong> Vaccination stands as a critical pillar of public health initiatives, safeguarding communities from a range of preventable infectious diseases. By administering vaccines, healthcare professionals help stimulate the body's immune response to develop immunity against specific pathogens. This not only protects vaccinated individuals but also contributes to herd immunity, limiting the spread of diseases within populations. Vaccination schedules are meticulously designed to ensure timely protection for people of all ages against illnesses like measles, influenza, and hepatitis, promoting healthier societies on a global scale.</p>
