                        <p></p>
                        <p>Our project aims to develop a digital healthcare management system that can facilitate the management of patients, medical records, appointments, and medication for hospitals and clinics. The system will be designed to provide an easy-to-use interface that can be accessed by healthcare providers, patients, and administrators. With the increasing demand for healthcare services and the need to streamline healthcare processes, our project will offer an efficient and effective solution that can help healthcare providers deliver high-quality care.</p>
                        <p></p>
                        <p>The current healthcare management system is largely paper-based and manual, leading to inefficiencies in managing patient data, scheduling appointments, and managing medications. This system is prone to errors and can lead to delays in patient care, missed appointments, and medication errors. In addition, the lack of a centralized database makes it difficult to share patient information between healthcare providers, leading to suboptimal care.</p>


